deck: Inspector for an Australian police department.
description:
Origin

An Australian police inspector.

Creation

Written by Chris Claremont and drawn by Rick Leonardi. The name clearly hearkens to the screen character Mick Dundee of the "Crocodile Dundee" franchise, though the characters are in no way related outside being from Australia. (The first movie had come out in 1986 with a sequel in 1988.)

Major Story Arcs

Mick Dundee accompanies Reg to a crime scene and find a bunch of Genoshan Magistrates tied up. The Magistrates refuse to talk to Mick so he and Reg book them and toss them in jail.
name: Mick Dundee

deck: The illegal child of two Genoshan mutants.
description:
Origin

Baby Boy was born on the wealthy island of Genosha. His parents were both known mutants and not allowed to "breed." They did so anyway and had a son that they never get to name. Baby Boy is presumed a mutant by the authorities because both parents were such.

Creation

Written by Chris Claremont and drawn by Rick Leonardi.

Major Story Arcs

When Genoshan Magistrates hear that Baby Boy has been born, they pursue the parents to punish them. The unnamed father leaves his wife's body in hopes of finding refuge for their son. The father carries Baby Boy to the airport and leaps over the fence with ease. Baby Boy is placed on a plane and leaves as the father is gunned down. Baby Boy is tracked, however, and is soon in the custody of the Genoshan Magistrates.
name: Baby Boy

deck: After getting her DNA mixed with that of a spider, Heather Brown's lifelong dream has come true, as she takes the identity of the superhero Spinnerette.
description:
Heather is socially awkward and geeky young woman. She is a huge comic fan and also has secret interest in role-playing games like D&D.

She is a biology graduate student, and are also working as a lab-assistant for Professor Lambha. After accidentally becoming the test subject for a genetic infusion chamber, Heather's DNA became mixed up with that of a spider, and she now has several spider-like abilities as well as six arms. Overjoyed, Heather decides to become a superhero.

Her dorm-mate Sahira did not like the idea of Heather being superhero, but decided to help her out anyway, like sewing her costumes. After a clumsy start, Heather manege to become team-mates with the heroes Mecha Maid and Tiger after taking down the villain Evil Spinnerette.

Powers & Abilities

Spinnerette has the strength of a spider, is immune to poison(except for alcohol), and is super-healing, along with having six arms and shoot web out of the base of her spine. She can use her arms to perform several actions at the same time with ease
name: Spinnerette

deck: Butler's estranged brother who is looking after Ellie Camacho.
name: Joshua Utler

description:
Origin

Ellie is the daughter of a woman Deadpool enjoyed a one night stand with. When he learned of her existence he dedicated himself and his loyal friends to tracking her down. Ellie was living with her adopted father, the decent-hearted brother of the evil scientist who had been tormenting Deadpool for years.

Creation

Ellie Camacho was created by Gerry Dugan, Declan Shelvy and Brian Posehn. She first appeared in a flashback in Deadpool Vol.3 issue 19 (2014), but was mentioned befrore. Her full first full appearance was during the "Original Sin" tie-in in Deadpool's own comic.

Major Story Arcs

Meeting her True Father

Unfortunately the terrorist group ULTIMATUM learned of Ellie's existence and went after her. Ellie's father had a weak heart and did not survive the strain of fleeing the terrorists. Deadpool rescued the child and she was adopted by S.H.I.E.L.D. Agent Preston and her family. She attends regular therapy sessions with a specialized child psychiatrist.

Not only is Ellie protected by Preston and her cyborg powers, she has magic on her side. The ghost of Benjamin Franklin and Michael, a Scottish magician, are both dear friends and have laid magical protections around her home.

Powers

Ellie is a mutant whose powers, like her father's, is to regenerate from damage. Unlike her father though, in order to heal, Ellie must die first. After her "death" she is then resurrected to the age when she first developed her abilities
